Learning: MCP prompts vs tools architecture difference

MCP Prompts (src/mcp/prompts.rs):
- Define PromptInfo with name, description, and PromptArguments
- Arguments are simple strings with no type/enum constraints
- Prompts generate PromptMessage content (user messages) - not direct actions
- Executed via get_prompt() which interpolates arguments into message text
- No validation or defaults on arguments

MCP Tools (src/mcp/tools.rs):
- Define ToolInfo with JSON Schema input_schema
- Strong type validation, enums, defaults, required fields
- Tools are invoked directly and perform actions
- call_tool() validates input against schema

Key takeaway: Use prompts for generating context/instructions, use tools for performing actions. Prompts lack the validation rigor of tools - keep them simple.